<ppt>
<slide>
<title>Web Application Attack Detection Using Hybrid Machine Learning</title>
<content>
- Presented by: [Your Name]
- Professor: [Professor’s Name]
- Date: August 27, 2025
</content>
</slide>
<slide>
<title>Problem Statement</title>
<content>
- Web applications face evolving attack threats
- Need for real-time, accurate, and interpretable detection
- Existing solutions lack adaptability and transparency
</content>
</slide>
<slide>
<title>Background & Research</title>
<content>
- Machine learning in cybersecurity
- Supervised vs. unsupervised models
- Importance of feature engineering and explainability
- Related work: strengths and gaps
</content>
</slide>
<slide>
<title>Methodology</title>
<content>
- Hybrid approach: XGBoost (supervised), Isolation Forest (unsupervised)
- Custom dataset generation (Burp Suite, mitmproxy, simulation scripts)
- Feature selection: payload length, user agent, behavioral scores
- Evaluation metrics: accuracy, precision, recall, F1-score, confusion matrix
</content>
</slide>
<slide>
<title>Implementation</title>
<content>
- Python, Flask backend
- Docker for deployment
- Integration with security tools
- SHAP for model interpretability
- Logging and feedback for retraining
</content>
</slide>
<slide>
<title>Results</title>
<content>
- Accuracy: ~84%
- Recall for attacks: 83%
- F1-score: 0.75
- Confusion matrix: strong detection, some false positives
- Feature importance and SHAP plots
- Balanced performance, low overfitting
</content>
</slide>
<slide>
<title>Limitations & Analysis</title>
<content>
- No latency, ROC-AUC, or public benchmarks measured
- Moderate precision for attacks (some false alarms)
- Misclassifications in ambiguous cases
- Need for periodic retraining
- Analysis supports technical viability and practical impact
</content>
</slide>
<slide>
<title>Conclusion & Future Work</title>
<content>
- Achieved real-time, interpretable attack detection
- Hybrid model adapts to new threats
- Supports security analysts with actionable insights
- Future work: operational metrics, feature diversity, improved anomaly handling
</content>
</slide>
</ppt>
